comments.body:
@DeepakKuPatro apologies for the frustrating experience during the beta. When you refresh tokens and some are already used, that indicates that your last message before the rate limit used more tokens than you had at the time.

 if you are building out a large project, I recommend upgrading to a higher tier plan that includes more tokens.

For info on our efforts to increase token efficiency follow issue #678. There are also a bunch of tips on how to work with Bolt more efficiently! These tips (including understanding the impact of project size) will be very relevant for you I believe.

Example: 

```
// Rest of the code remains the same...

export default function ProductOverview() {
  // ... (rest of the component code)

  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto p-4">
      {/* ... (rest of the JSX) */}
```
